      "span_text": "A systematic review of 89 studies evaluating the stool antigen test found an aggregate sensitivity and specificity of 91% and 93%, respectively.  Stool samples must be stored at −20°C prior to testing for this test to be accurate; the sensitivity of the stool antigen test decreases to 69% after storage of the samples at room temperature for 2-3 days."
